XML = eXtensible Markup Language
We use XML to define the meaning of the data in the file.
We can define our own tags and attributes to define the data and it's structure.

HTML = HyperText Markup Language
We use HTML to define the presentation of the data in the file.
Each HTML tag has a specific meaning and is 
used to display the data in a specific way.
HTML tags are predefined and cannot be changed.
-->
